    • Method Detail

      • placeLifeForm

        public void placeLifeForm(ALifeForm lf)
        Places the specified LifeForm in the map. The method will search for an empty map space to place the LifeForm in first before overwritting other non-LifeForm world objects.
        Parameters:
        lf - - LifeForm to place in the world.

      • placeFood

        public void placeFood(boolean reset)
        Places the food objects on the map based on the food density value specified by the user. Won't place food over LifeForms and decides whether or not to override other world objects. If reset is true or the food list is empty the list will be cleared and a new list of food objects will be created, otherwise the existing food objects in the list will be re-placed.
        Parameters:
        reset - - whether or not to reset the food list

      • placeObstacles

        public void placeObstacles(boolean reset)
        Places the obstalces on the map based on the obstacle density value specified by the user. Won't place obstacles over LifeForms and decides whether or not to override other world objects. If reset is true or the obstacle list is empty the list will be cleared and a new list of obstacles will be created, otherwise the existing obstacles in the list will be re-placed.
        Parameters:
        reset - - whether or not to reset the obstacle list

      • clearMap

        public void clearMap()
        Sets all values in the map array to null.

      • decide

        public boolean decide(double denominator)
        Performs a decision based on a given denominator used to create a threshold by dividing 1 by the parameter. If a randomly generated number is lower than the threshold the method will return true.
        Returns:
        true if random number is lower than 1 / denominator.

      • save

        public void save()
        Saves the world by serialising it and writing it to a file, including all objects contained within the world.

      • load

        public void load(Configuration config)
        Loads values in to the world from a world file using the given configuration file.
        Parameters:
        config - - configuration file to use when loading the world.

      • syncConfiguration
